---
import Breadcrumb from '../components/layout/Breadcrumb.astro';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  description="Terms of Services for PAL Portals - Agreement governing your use of our GenAI solutions and digital services."
  title="Terms of Services | PAL Portals"
>
  <Breadcrumb>
    <Fragment slot="title">Terms of Services</Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="description">Complete terms and conditions governing your use of PAL Portals services, including service agreements, user responsibilities, and service level expectations.</Fragment>
  </Breadcrumb>

  <section class="py-16 lg:py-20">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
        <!-- Introduction -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">Terms of Services</h1>
          <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 text-lg">
            <strong>Effective Date:</strong> January 2, 2026
          </p>
          <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mt-4">
            These Terms of Services ("Terms," "Agreement," or "ToS") constitute a legally binding agreement between PAL Portals ("Company," "Service Provider," "we," "us," or "our") and you ("Client," "User," "you," or "your"). These Terms govern your access to, use of, and interaction with our website, services, products, and any related materials (collectively, "Services").
          </p>
          <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mt-4">
            By accessing, browsing, or using our Services, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms, as well as our Privacy Policy and Legal Notice. If you do not agree with any provision, you must immediately cease use of our Services.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 1. Service Description -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">1. Service Description</h2>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">1.1 Services Offered</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mb-4">
              PAL Portals provides GenAI-powered digital solutions and services, including but not limited to:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 list-disc list-inside">
              <li>Generative AI consultation and strategy</li>
              <li>Custom AI model development and implementation</li>
              <li>Data analysis and insights using AI technologies</li>
              <li>Workflow automation and process optimization</li>
              <li>AI-powered content generation and summarization</li>
              <li>Integration of AI tools with existing business systems</li>
              <li>Training and support for AI implementation</li>
              <li>Consulting and advisory services related to AI adoption</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">1.2 Service Scope</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              The specific scope of services will be defined in individual service agreements, project proposals, or statement of work (SOW) documents. The descriptions on our Website are general overviews and do not constitute binding service commitments unless explicitly stated in a signed contract.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2. Eligibility and Account Creation -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">2. Eligibility and Account Creation</h2>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">2.1 Eligibility Requirements</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              To use our Services, you must:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 list-disc list-inside mt-3">
              <li>Be at least 18 years of age (or the age of majority in your jurisdiction)</li>
              <li>Have the legal capacity to enter into binding agreements</li>
              <li>Reside in a jurisdiction where our Services are lawfully offered</li>
              <li>Not be subject to any sanctions or export restrictions</li>
              <li>Not have been previously suspended or terminated from our Services</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">2.2 Account Registration</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mb-3">
              If you create an account with PAL Portals, you agree to:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 list-disc list-inside">
              <li>Provide accurate, complete, and truthful information during registration</li>
              <li>Keep your account credentials confidential and secure</li>
              <li>Immediately notify us of any unauthorized access or use</li>
              <li>Maintain and promptly update your account information</li>
              <li>Take full responsibility for all activities under your account</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">2.3 Account Termination</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              PAL Portals reserves the right to suspend or terminate your account at any time for violations of these Terms, non-payment, fraudulent activity, or other reasons at our sole discretion. Account termination may result in loss of access to your data, projects, and services.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 3. Payment Terms and Pricing -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">3. Payment Terms and Pricing</h2>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">3.1 Pricing and Fees</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mb-4">
              Pricing for our Services is as follows:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 list-disc list-inside">
              <li>Base service fees as quoted in our pricing page or service agreement</li>
              <li>Additional charges for extra features, modules, or usage beyond included limits</li>
              <li>Implementation and setup fees (if applicable)</li>
              <li>Support and maintenance fees</li>
              <li>All applicable taxes (GST in India, VAT/Sales Tax in other jurisdictions)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">3.2 Payment Methods and Schedule</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mb-3">
              Payment may be made through:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 list-disc list-inside mb-4">
              <li>Bank transfer / Wire transfer</li>
              <li>Credit/Debit card (processed through secure payment gateways)</li>
              <li>Online payment platforms (Stripe, PayPal, etc.)</li>
              <li>Other methods agreed upon in writing</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              Invoices are issued according to the billing cycle specified in your service agreement (monthly, quarterly, or annually). Payment is due within 30 days of invoice date unless otherwise agreed in writing.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">3.3 Late Payments</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              If payment is not received by the due date, we may:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 list-disc list-inside mt-3 mb-4">
              <li>Charge late payment interest at 1.5% per month (18% per annum) or the maximum rate allowed by law</li>
              <li>Suspend or terminate your access to Services</li>
              <li>Pursue legal action to recover outstanding amounts</li>
              <li>Recover collection costs and legal fees</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">3.4 Currency and Taxes</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              All prices are quoted in USD unless otherwise specified. You are responsible for any currency conversion fees. All prices exclude applicable taxes, which will be added based on your location and tax status.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 4. Service Delivery and Performance -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">4. Service Delivery and Performance</h2>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">4.1 Service Level Agreement (SLA)</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mb-3">
              For premium services, PAL Portals commits to:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 list-disc list-inside">
              <li><strong>Availability:</strong> 99.5% uptime for cloud-hosted services (excludes scheduled maintenance)</li>
              <li><strong>Support Response Time:</strong> Critical issues within 2 hours; High priority within 8 hours; Normal priority within 24 hours</li>
              <li><strong>Project Delivery:</strong> As specified in the project SOW with agreed-upon milestones</li>
              <li><strong>Performance Standards:</strong> As defined in individual service agreements</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">4.2 Exclusions from SLA</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              SLA commitments do not apply to:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 list-disc list-inside mt-3">
              <li>Scheduled maintenance and updates</li>
              <li>Service disruptions caused by client actions or misuse</li>
              <li>Third-party service failures or issues beyond our control</li>
              <li>Force majeure events (natural disasters, pandemics, etc.)</li>
              <li>Network issues on the client's end</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">4.3 Maintenance and Updates</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              PAL Portals may perform scheduled maintenance, updates, or patches without prior notice. We will endeavor to minimize disruption and notify clients of critical maintenance in advance when possible.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 5. Intellectual Property -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">5. Intellectual Property</h2>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">5.1 PAL Portals IP Rights</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              All intellectual property related to our Services, including software, algorithms, documentation, and methodologies, remains the exclusive property of PAL Portals or its licensors. You are granted a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use these materials solely for the purpose of accessing and using our Services.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">5.2 Client Data and Output</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mb-4">
              <strong>Client Data Ownership:</strong> You retain all rights to your input data, content, and information provided to PAL Portals.
            </p>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mb-4">
              <strong>Service Output:</strong> Reports, analyses, and deliverables created by PAL Portals for your Services are provided for your use. The underlying AI models, processes, and methodologies remain our intellectual property.
            </p>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              <strong>Restrictions:</strong> You may not reverse engineer, decompile, or attempt to extract our proprietary algorithms or models from the outputs.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">5.3 Feedback and Suggestions</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              By providing feedback, suggestions, or ideas about our Services, you grant PAL Portals the right to use this feedback to improve our Services without attribution or compensation.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 6. Confidentiality -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">6. Confidentiality</h2>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">6.1 Confidential Information</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              Both parties agree to maintain the confidentiality of any proprietary or sensitive information shared during the provision of Services. This includes business plans, trade secrets, client lists, and technical information.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">6.2 Data Protection</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              PAL Portals implements industry-standard security measures to protect your data. However, we cannot guarantee absolute security against all threats. You acknowledge the inherent risks of transmitting data over the internet.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">6.3 Use of Your Data</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              We will not use your data for any purpose other than providing Services, unless we obtain your explicit written consent. See our Privacy Policy for detailed information on data handling.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 7. User Obligations and Conduct -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">7. User Obligations and Conduct</h2>
          
          <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mb-4">
            You agree to:
          </p>

          <ul class="space-y-3 text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Use our Services only for lawful purposes in compliance with all applicable laws</li>
            <li>Not engage in any form of harassment, abuse, or threatening behavior</li>
            <li>Not attempt to gain unauthorized access to our systems or networks</li>
            <li>Not introduce viruses, malware, or harmful code</li>
            <li>Not engage in automated scraping or data extraction</li>
            <li>Not resell, redistribute, or sublicense our Services without written permission</li>
            <li>Not use our Services for illegal activities or to violate third-party rights</li>
            <li>Comply with all laws regarding data protection, privacy, and export controls</li>
            <li>Maintain compliance with your industry's regulatory requirements when using our Services</li>
            <li>Provide accurate and complete information during onboarding and throughout the engagement</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- 8. Limitation of Liability -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          
          <div class="p-4 bg-yellow-50 dark:bg-yellow-900/20 border border-yellow-200 dark:border-yellow-800 rounded-lg mb-6">
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              <strong>DISCLAIMER:</strong> TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, PAL PORTALS SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, PUNITIVE, OR EXEMPLARY DAMAGES ARISING FROM YOUR USE OF OR INABILITY TO USE OUR SERVICES.
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mb-6">
            This includes damages for loss of profits, revenue, data, goodwill, business interruption, or any other loss, even if PAL Portals has been advised of the possibility of such damages.
          </p>

          <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
            <strong>Maximum Liability Cap:</strong> Our total liability to you for any claim arising from these Terms shall not exceed the total amount paid by you in the 12 months preceding the claim, or USD $100, whichever is greater.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 9. Indemnification -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">9. Indemnification</h2>
          
          <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
            You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless PAL Portals, its officers, directors, employees, and agents from any and all claims, losses, damages, liabilities, and expenses (including attorneys' fees) arising from:
          </p>

          <ul class="space-y-3 text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 list-disc list-inside mt-4">
            <li>Your violation of these Terms or applicable laws</li>
            <li>Your use or misuse of our Services</li>
            <li>Your violation of intellectual property rights</li>
            <li>Content you provide or actions you take using our Services</li>
            <li>Claims by third parties related to your use of the Services</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- 10. Termination -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">10. Termination</h2>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">10.1 Termination by You</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              You may terminate your use of our Services by providing written notice. However, you remain responsible for all charges incurred through the date of termination.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">10.2 Termination by PAL Portals</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              PAL Portals may terminate or suspend Services immediately if you:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 list-disc list-inside mt-3">
              <li>Violate any provision of these Terms</li>
              <li>Engage in illegal or fraudulent activity</li>
              <li>Fail to pay invoices within 60 days of due date</li>
              <li>Use our Services to harm others or violate laws</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">10.3 Effect of Termination</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              Upon termination, your right to use the Services ceases immediately. You remain responsible for all outstanding charges. PAL Portals is not responsible for data loss following termination.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 11. Warranty Disclaimers -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">11. Warranty Disclaimers</h2>
          
          <div class="p-4 bg-yellow-50 dark:bg-yellow-900/20 border border-yellow-200 dark:border-yellow-800 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mb-4">
              <strong>AS-IS BASIS:</strong> Our Services are provided on an "AS IS" and "AS AVAILABLE" basis without any warranties, express or implied.
            </p>

            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              PAL Portals disclaims all warranties including:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 list-disc list-inside mt-3">
              <li>Warranties of merchantability or fitness for a particular purpose</li>
              <li>Warranties that Services will be uninterrupted or error-free</li>
              <li>Warranties regarding accuracy, completeness, or timeliness of outputs</li>
              <li>Warranties that AI-generated content is original or legally risk-free</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 12. Refund Policy -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">12. Refund Policy</h2>
          
          <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mb-4">
            <strong>No Refunds:</strong> All payments made for Services are non-refundable except as required by law. This includes:
          </p>

          <ul class="space-y-2 text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 list-disc list-inside mb-6">
            <li>Subscription fees for completed billing periods</li>
            <li>Upfront payments for services rendered</li>
            <li>Implementation or setup fees</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
            <strong>Exceptions:</strong> Refunds may be considered in cases of service failures meeting the SLA criteria, at PAL Portals' sole discretion. Any refund claim must be submitted in writing within 30 days of the service failure.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 13. Governing Law and Dispute Resolution -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">13. Governing Law and Dispute Resolution</h2>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">13.1 Governing Law</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India, without regard to its conflict of law provisions. However, mandatory local laws in your jurisdiction may apply where applicable.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">13.2 Dispute Resolution Process</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mb-3">
              Before initiating legal proceedings:
            </p>
            <ol class="space-y-2 text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 list-decimal list-inside">
              <li>Submit a written complaint to legal@palportals.com describing the dispute</li>
              <li>Engage in good-faith negotiations for 30 days</li>
              <li>If unresolved, either party may seek arbitration or litigation</li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark dark:text-white mb-3">13.3 Jurisdiction</h3>
            <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
              You consent to the exclusive jurisdiction of courts in India. However, if you are a consumer in a jurisdiction with mandatory local courts, you may bring disputes in those courts as permitted by local law.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 14. Modifications to Terms -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">14. Modifications to Terms</h2>
          
          <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6">
            PAL Portals may modify these Terms at any time. Changes will be effective immediately upon posting to our Website. Continued use of our Services following modifications constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms. For material changes, we will provide prior notice where possible.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 15. Third-Party Services and Links -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark dark:text-white mb-4">15. Third-Party Services and Links</h2>
          
          <p class="text-body-color dark:text-dark-6 mb-4">
            Our Services may integrate with or link to third-party services, APIs, or platforms. PAL Portals does not control, endorse, or assume responsibility for third-party services. Your use of such services is subject to their terms and conditions.
          </p>

          <div class="p-4 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20 rounded-lg">
